{% comment %}
  Konnected accent CSS custom properties, sourced from the theme color palette.

  Horizon v4 replaced the per-scheme color model with a single `color_palette`
  and dropped the `--color-primary` / `--color-foreground-heading` custom
  properties that v3 emitted per scheme. Konnected content and custom blocks
  (text-icon, timeline, tables, reseller/installer items, header buttons,
  grid-section headings) still consume them, so we define them here from the
  palette's `brand` entry — a single source of truth the merchant edits in the
  theme editor's color palette.
{% endcomment %}
{% style %}
  :root {
    --color-primary: {{ settings.color_palette.brand }};
    --color-primary-rgb: {{ settings.color_palette.brand.rgb }};
    --color-primary-hover: {{ settings.color_palette.brand }};
    --color-primary-active: {{ settings.color_palette.brand }};
    /* Headings track the section's contextual foreground (dark on light,
       light on dark) rather than a fixed color. */
    --color-foreground-heading: var(--color-foreground);
  }
{% endstyle %}
